  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in South Dakota for FY2026 to date total $439M. There were 2,535 awards with an average award size of $173K. Obligations fell 45.4% year over year. Fiscal-year comparisons show previous totals of $624M in FY21, $1.2B in FY22, $1B in FY23, $1.3B in FY24, and $804M in FY25, with the current FY26 to date figure at $439M. The largest buying agencies so far are the Department of Defense at $172M, the Department of Health and Human Services at $96.8M, and the Department of the Interior at $82.8M. Top vendors by obligations to date include KBR WYLE SERVICES, LLC at $63.3M, FEDERAL CONTRACTING INC at $40.3M, and BL HARBERT INTERNATIONAL LLC at $30.7M. Leading NAICS categories by obligations include Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $92.1M and Computer Facilities Management Services at $63.7M. All figures are contract obligations and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
