        "heading": "How large is the FY2026 to date federal footprint in South Dakota?",
        "body": "Total obligations are $439M across 2,535 awards, with an average award size of $173K. Obligations fell 45.4% year over year, and the FY26 to date total is smaller than FY25 at $804M and FY24 at $1.3B."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors account for the bulk of FY2026 obligations?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense accounts for $172M of obligations, followed by the Department of Health and Human Services at $96.8M and the Department of the Interior at $82.8M. Top vendors are KBR WYLE SERVICES, LLC at $63.3M, FEDERAL CONTRACTING INC at $40.3M, and BL HARBERT INTERNATIONAL LLC at $30.7M."
      }
    ]
